{
 "response": "# Perspective Audit \u2014 Interactive Map With Mouse-Only Navigation\n\n## Step 1 \u2014 Escalated perspectives confirmed\n\n| Perspective | Incoming alarm | Reviewed here |\n|---|---|---|\n| Magnification & Reflow | HIGH | Yes |\n| Keyboard & Motor Access | HIGH | Yes |\n| Screen Reader & Semantic Structure | MEDIUM | Yes |\n\n**Not escalated \u2014 not reviewed (no checklist run):** Environmental Contrast, Vestibular & Motion Sensitivity, Auditory Access, Cognitive & Neurodivergent. No `<video>`/`<audio>`, no animation (`.map-canvas { transition: none }`), and no auth/multi-step flow appears in scope, so the LOW ratings are not contested from this pass.\n\nEvidence is cited against the artifact under review, `map-interface-zoom-user.md`, at the embedded component's line numbers.\n\n---\n\n## Perspective 1 \u2014 Magnification & Reflow (HIGH)\n\n**WCAG (AA):** 1.4.4, 1.4.10, 1.4.12, 1.4.13, 2.4.11\n\n### JTBD checklist\n\n| # | Item | Result |\n|---|---|---|\n| 1 | Reflow to 320px equivalent, no horizontal scrollbar (1.4.10) | **FINDING** \u2014 fixed 280px input (+padding) and absolutely-offset zoom controls |\n| 2 | Focused elements never obscured by sticky/fixed chrome (2.4.11) | **PASS** \u2014 no sticky/fixed banners; search and zoom controls stay visible when focused |\n| 3 | Text scales to 200% without overflow/truncation (1.4.4) | **FINDING** \u2014 fixed 18px control boxes and 200px/13px popup inside `overflow:hidden` |\n| 4 | Adapts to text-spacing overrides (1.4.12) | **FINDING** \u2014 fixed-width popup in a fixed-height clipped container |\n| 5 | Hover/focus content dismissible + hoverable + persistent (1.4.13) | **FINDING** \u2014 hover-only popup, no Escape, no focus trigger |\n\n### Findings\n\n**Finding:** Marker info popups appear only on `onMouseEnter` and are removed on `onMouseLeave`. There is no Escape-to-dismiss and no focus/click path to trigger them, so a magnifier user who pans the viewport away from the marker (or who cannot hold a steady hover on a 24px pin at high magnification) loses the content and cannot recall it without re-hovering. \"Hoverable\" and \"persistent\" technically pass because the popup is a DOM child of the marker, but \"dismissible\" fails and there is no non-pointer trigger.\n**WCAG:** 1.4.13 Content on Hover or Focus\n**Perspective:** Magnification & Reflow\n**Severity:** MAJOR\n**Route to:** UX Design (secondary: Front-End Dev)\n**Evidence:** `map-interface-zoom-user.md:88-98` \u2014 `onMouseEnter={() => setActivePopup(m.id)} onMouseLeave={() => setActivePopup(null)}`; popup rendered only while `activePopup === m.id`. No `keydown`/Escape handler anywhere in the component.\n**Fix:** Trigger the popup on focus as well as hover, keep it open until Escape or focus-out (not on a timer), and ensure the pointer can travel onto it. Pair with the keyboard-focusability fix in Perspective 5 so the same markup serves both users.\n\n**Finding:** Content does not reflow at a 320px CSS width. The search input is a fixed `width: 280px` with `8px 12px` padding (\u2248304px border-box) inside a page with `padding: 24px` (48px total), forcing \u2248352px of horizontal content and a horizontal scrollbar at 320px. Separately, the zoom controls are pinned with `position: absolute; top: 8px; right: 8px` and, as authored, overlap the map content area rather than reflowing.\n**WCAG:** 1.4.10 Reflow\n**Perspective:** Magnification & Reflow\n**Severity:** MAJOR\n**Route to:** Visual Design (secondary: Front-End Dev)\n**Evidence:** `map-interface-zoom-user.md:123-125` (`.search-input { width: 280px; padding: 8px 12px }`), `:118` (`.map-page { padding: 24px }`), `:161-164` (`.map-controls { position: absolute; top: 8px; right: 8px }`).\n**Fix:** Use `max-width: 100%` (or `width: 100%` with a `max-width`) on the search input and `box-sizing: border-box`; let controls sit in flow or use logical insets that don't overlap content at narrow widths. Verify with a 320px-wide reflow screenshot.\n\n**Finding:** Text-only zoom to 200% is not accommodated. The `+`/`\u2212` glyphs sit in fixed `18px \u00d7 18px` boxes with `font-size: 14px`, and the marker popup is a fixed `width: 200px` with `font-size: 13px`. Because `.map-container` is `overflow: hidden` with a fixed `height: 400px`, enlarged glyphs and wrapped popup text are clipped rather than expanding.\n**WCAG:** 1.4.4 Resize Text\n**Perspective:** Magnification & Reflow\n**Severity:** MINOR\n**Route to:** Visual Design (secondary: Front-End Dev)\n**Evidence:** `map-interface-zoom-user.md:166-172` (`.zoom-control { width: 18px; height: 18px; font-size: 14px }`), `:149-157` (`.marker-popup { width: 200px }`, `p { font-size: 13px }`), `:128-132` (`.map-container { overflow: hidden; height: 400px }`).\n**Fix:** Size controls in relative units with `min-width/min-height` at least `24px` (see 2.5.8), allow the popup to grow (`max-width` + wrap), and avoid clipping popups against `overflow: hidden`.\n\n**Finding:** User text-spacing overrides (1.5\u00d7 line-height, 2\u00d7 paragraph, 0.12em letter, 0.16em word) enlarge the popup's text block, but the `200px` fixed width inside the `overflow: hidden`, fixed-height container risks clipping the info text with no scroll recovery.\n**WCAG:** 1.4.12 Text Spacing\n**Perspective:** Magnification & Reflow\n**Severity:** MINOR\n**Route to:** Visual Design (secondary: Front-End Dev)\n**Evidence:** `map-interface-zoom-user.md:149-154` (`.marker-popup { width: 200px }`), `:128-132` (`overflow: hidden`).\n**Fix:** Let the popup container grow with content and escape the clipped map bounds (e.g., render in a portal/overlay layer) so spacing overrides don't truncate.\n\n### Red flags checked\n- Two-axis scrolling at 320px \u2014 not triggered (`overflow: hidden`, drag-pan). Not fired.\n- Text completely hidden/overlapping at 200% \u2014 control/content overlap and clipping observed but not total text loss; captured as MAJOR/MINOR above, not auto-CRITICAL.\n- Tooltip disappears before magnifier user can reach it \u2014 popup is a child of the marker so it is reachable while hovered; captured as the 1.4.13 MAJOR (dismiss/trigger gap), not auto-CRITICAL.\n\nAll findings are code-level (enforceable from source).\n\n---\n\n## Perspective 5 \u2014 Keyboard & Motor Access (HIGH)\n\n**WCAG (AA):** 1.3.4, 2.1.1, 2.1.2, 2.4.1, 2.4.3, 2.4.7, 2.4.13, 2.5.1, 2.5.2, 2.5.3, 2.5.7, 2.5.8\n\n### JTBD checklist\n\n| # | Item | Result |\n|---|---|---|\n| 1 | All interactive elements keyboard-operable (2.1.1) | **FINDING (red flag)** \u2014 pan and marker info are pointer-only |\n| 2 | No keyboard trap (2.1.2) | **PASS** \u2014 container is not focusable and adds no key handlers; focus flows search \u2192 zoom-in \u2192 zoom-out |\n| 3 | Skip link to main (2.4.1) | **N/A** \u2014 single embedded component; no repeated blocks in scope |\n| 4 | Focus order logical (2.4.3) | **PASS** \u2014 DOM order search \u2192 zoom-in \u2192 zoom-out is coherent |\n| 5 | Focus indicator \u22652px, \u22653:1 (2.4.7, 2.4.13) | **PASS** \u2014 `outline: 3px`/`2px solid #005fcc` on the focusable controls |\n| 6 | Multipoint/path gestures have single-pointer alt (2.5.1) | **FINDING** \u2014 pan is a path-based drag with no alternative |\n| 7 | Activation on up-event / abortable (2.5.2) | **PASS** \u2014 buttons fire on `onClick`; drag start on mousedown falls under essential direct-manipulation |\n| 8 | Visible label matches accessible name (2.5.3) | **FINDING** \u2014 `+`/`\u2212` glyphs vs `aria-label` \"Zoom in\"/\"Zoom out\" |\n| 9 | Every drag has a click-based alternative (2.5.7) | **FINDING (red flag)** \u2014 pan is drag-only |\n| 10 | Targets \u226524\u00d724 with spacing (2.5.8) | **FINDING** \u2014 zoom buttons 18\u00d718, `gap: 2px` |\n| 11 | Portrait and landscape (1.3.4) | **PASS** \u2014 no orientation lock |\n\n### Findings\n\n**Finding:** Map panning is bound exclusively to `onMouseDown/Move/Up`, and marker info is bound exclusively to `onMouseEnter/Leave`. The markers are plain `<div>`s with no `tabIndex`, `role`, or key handlers, so a keyboard user cannot pan the map and cannot reach or reveal any marker's details. Zoom is the only keyboard-operable map function (via the `<button>`s). Essential functionality is keyboard-inoperable.\n**WCAG:** 2.1.1 Keyboard\n**Perspective:** Keyboard & Motor Access\n**Severity:** CRITICAL\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: UX Design)\n**Evidence:** `map-interface-zoom-user.md:33-46` (mouse-only pan handlers), `:88-89` (marker `onMouseEnter/onMouseLeave`), `:82-91` (marker is a `<div>` with no `tabIndex`/`role`/keydown).\n**Fix:** Make markers focusable interactive elements (`<button>`, or `tabindex=\"0\"` + `role=\"button\"`) that toggle the popup on Enter/Space and Escape; add a keyboard pan model (arrow keys move the offset when the map region has focus, with a documented key contract) or provide discrete pan controls.\n**Red flag fired:** \"Interactive element unreachable by keyboard\" \u2192 CRITICAL.\n\n**Finding:** Panning requires a click-and-drag (a dragging, path-based movement). There is no single-pointer, non-drag, non-path alternative \u2014 no pan buttons, no click-to-recenter. This blocks users who can operate a pointer but cannot perform a sustained drag or trace a path (tremor, switch/head-pointer, touch users with limited dexterity).\n**WCAG:** 2.5.7 Dragging Movements (primary); 2.5.1 Pointer Gestures (path-based, also fails)\n**Perspective:** Keyboard & Motor Access\n**Severity:** CRITICAL\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: UX Design)\n**Evidence:** `map-interface-zoom-user.md:33-46` \u2014 pan derived from `e.clientX/clientY` deltas across mousedown\u2192mousemove\u2192mouseup; no click/tap equivalent exists in the component.\n**Fix:** Add a non-drag alternative: directional pan buttons and/or click-a-marker-to-center, plus the keyboard arrow-pan from the 2.1.1 fix. A single-pointer tap alternative satisfies 2.5.7 and 2.5.1 together.\n**Red flag fired:** \"Drag-only interaction with no click alternative\" \u2192 CRITICAL.\n\n**Finding:** Zoom control targets are `18px \u00d7 18px` \u2014 below the 24\u00d724 CSS px minimum \u2014 and are stacked with only `gap: 2px`, so the undersized-target spacing exception is not met either.\n**WCAG:** 2.5.8 Target Size (Minimum)\n**Perspective:** Keyboard & Motor Access\n**Severity:** MAJOR\n**Route to:** Visual Design (secondary: Front-End Dev)\n**Evidence:** `map-interface-zoom-user.md:166-168` (`.zoom-control { width: 18px; height: 18px }`), `:161-164` (`.map-controls { gap: 2px }`).\n**Fix:** Increase each control to \u226524\u00d724 CSS px (44\u00d744 recommended for touch) and increase spacing so each target has a 24px non-overlapping spacing circle.\n\n**Finding:** The zoom buttons present the visible glyphs `+` and `\u2212` but expose accessible names \"Zoom in\" / \"Zoom out.\" The visible label text is not contained in the accessible name, so a speech-input user saying \"click plus\" / \"click minus\" (matching what they see) will not activate the control.\n**WCAG:** 2.5.3 Label in Name\n**Perspective:** Keyboard & Motor Access\n**Severity:** MINOR\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: Content Author)\n**Evidence:** `map-interface-zoom-user.md:106-107` \u2014 `aria-label=\"Zoom in\"` on a button whose text node is `+`; `aria-label=\"Zoom out\"` on a button whose text node is `\u2212`.\n**Fix:** Make the accessible name contain the visible affordance (e.g., `aria-label=\"Zoom in (+)\"`) or add visually-hidden text alongside the glyph so the spoken and rendered labels align.\n\n### Red flags checked\n- Interactive element unreachable by keyboard \u2014 **FIRED** (pan + markers) \u2192 CRITICAL above.\n- Keyboard trap \u2014 not present (no focus-capturing handlers). Not fired.\n- Drag-only interaction with no click alternative \u2014 **FIRED** (pan) \u2192 CRITICAL above.\n- `outline: none/0` with no replacement \u2014 not present; explicit focus styles exist (`:126`, `:174`). Not fired.\n\nAll findings are code-level (enforceable from source).\n\n---\n\n## Perspective 6 \u2014 Screen Reader & Semantic Structure (MEDIUM)\n\n**WCAG (AA):** 1.1.1, 1.3.1, 1.3.2, 2.4.2, 2.4.4, 2.4.6, 3.1.1, 3.1.2, 3.3.1, 3.3.2, 4.1.2, 4.1.3\n\n### JTBD checklist\n\n| # | Item | Result |\n|---|---|---|\n| 1 | Landmarks present/correct (1.3.1) | **FINDING (MINOR)** \u2014 `<section>` has no accessible name; relies on host for `<main>` |\n| 2 | Heading hierarchy, h1 present (2.4.6) | **PASS** \u2014 single `<h1>Our Locations</h1>` |\n| 3 | Informative img alt / decorative alt=\"\" (1.1.1) | **FINDING** \u2014 marker label carried by `aria-label` on a generic `<div>` |\n| 4 | DOM order matches visual reading order (1.3.2) | **PASS** \u2014 markers in list order; control-after-canvas order not meaning-breaking |\n| 5 | Unique descriptive `<title>` (2.4.2) | **N/A** \u2014 document title owned by host page |\n| 6 | Link text describes destination (2.4.4) | **N/A** \u2014 no links |\n| 7 | `lang` on `<html>` (3.1.1) | **N/A** \u2014 component does not render `<html>` |\n| 8 | Foreign-language phrases tagged (3.1.2) | **N/A** \u2014 none present |\n| 9 | Inputs have associated visible label (3.3.2) | **PASS** \u2014 `<label for=\"location-search\">` bound to `#location-search` |\n| 10 | Errors identify field via `aria-describedby` (3.3.1) | **N/A** \u2014 no validation/error state implemented |\n| 11 | Custom widgets use correct ARIA roles (4.1.2) | **FINDING (red flag)** + **FINDING** \u2014 markers have no role/name/state; `role=\"application\"` misused |\n| 12 | Status messages via `aria-live` (4.1.3) | **FINDING (MINOR)** \u2014 zoom state changes are silent |\n| 13 | SPA route changes managed | **N/A** \u2014 no routing |\n\n### Findings\n\n**Finding:** The map's actual content \u2014 the three locations and their details (`m.info`: hours, headcount, square footage) \u2014 is unreachable by a screen reader. The detail text is rendered only while `activePopup === m.id` (pointer hover), so it is absent from the accessibility tree for AT users. The markers are non-focusable `<div>`s with no `role`, and their labels are supplied by `aria-label` on an element with an implicit `generic` role, where `aria-label` is not reliably exposed. With `role=\"application\"` on the container suppressing the screen reader's browse/reading cursor, an AT user reaches a region announced as \"Interactive map showing office locations\" with nothing enumerable inside it. The information the component exists to convey is effectively inaccessible. There is no equivalent text list of locations elsewhere in the component.\n**WCAG:** 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value (with 1.1.1 Non-text Content for the pin/label)\n**Perspective:** Screen Reader & Semantic Structure\n**Severity:** CRITICAL\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: Content Author)\n**Evidence:** `map-interface-zoom-user.md:82-98` \u2014 marker `<div>` (no `role`/`tabIndex`), `aria-label` on `.marker-pin` `<div>` (`:91`), detail block gated on `activePopup === m.id` (`:93-98`); `:66` `role=\"application\"`.\n**Fix:** Expose the locations as real content: focusable interactive markers with an accessible name (label) that reveal their info in the accessibility tree (not gated on hover-only rendering), and/or provide a persistent semantic list of the same locations and details as a text equivalent. Move the `aria-label` onto an element with an appropriate role.\n**Red flag fired:** \"Custom widget with no ARIA role\" (the interactive markers) \u2192 CRITICAL. *Calibration note: I am rating this CRITICAL rather than MAJOR because the map is the sole carrier of the location data in this component \u2014 there is no text fallback \u2014 so a screen-reader user is blocked from the component's purpose, which meets \"blocks access entirely\" for this perspective. If a redundant text list of the same locations exists elsewhere on the host page, this drops to MAJOR. That dependency is the honest boundary of the CRITICAL call, and it argues the incoming MEDIUM alarm under-weighted this perspective.*\n\n**Finding:** `role=\"application\"` is applied to the map container, but no keyboard interaction model is implemented \u2014 no focusable descendants, no key handlers, no managed focus. `role=\"application\"` instructs the screen reader to hand nearly all keystrokes to the widget and disable normal reading commands; applied to a widget the user cannot operate, it removes the reading tools the user needs and gives nothing operable in return.\n**WCAG:** 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value\n**Perspective:** Screen Reader & Semantic Structure\n**Severity:** MAJOR\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: UX Design)\n**Evidence:** `map-interface-zoom-user.md:63-73` \u2014 `role=\"application\"` with only mouse/wheel handlers and no keyboard/focus implementation.\n**Fix:** Remove `role=\"application\"` unless and until a full keyboard interaction model exists. Prefer `role=\"group\"`/`role=\"region\"` with an accessible name (see landmark finding) plus genuinely focusable, operable controls.\n\n**Finding:** Zoom in/out are the only screen-reader-operable map controls, but activating them produces no announced result \u2014 `zoomLevel` changes with no `aria-live` status. An AT user pressing \"Zoom in\" gets no confirmation the map changed.\n**WCAG:** 4.1.3 Status Messages\n**Perspective:** Screen Reader & Semantic Structure\n**Severity:** MINOR\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: UX Design)\n**Evidence:** `map-interface-zoom-user.md:106-107` (`setZoomLevel(...)`) with no `aria-live` region rendered anywhere in the component.\n**Fix:** Add a polite live region announcing the new zoom level/scale after each change (e.g., \"Zoom 150%\").\n\n**Finding:** The component's outer container is a bare `<section>` with no accessible name, so it is not exposed as a labeled region, and the component provides no `<main>`. At component scope the host page is expected to supply `<main>`, so this is not the \"no `<main>` \u2192 CRITICAL\" red flag \u2014 it is a MINOR structural gap.\n**WCAG:** 1.3.1 Info and Relationships\n**Perspective:** Screen Reader & Semantic Structure\n**Severity:** MINOR\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: UX Design)\n**Evidence:** `map-interface-zoom-user.md:55` \u2014 `<section className=\"map-page\">` with no `aria-label`/`aria-labelledby`.\n**Fix:** Give the section an accessible name (e.g., `aria-labelledby` referencing the `<h1>`) so it forms a discoverable region, and ensure the host wraps the component in `<main>`.\n\n### Red flags checked\n- No `<main>` landmark \u2014 **not fired.** Deliberately not auto-CRITICAL: this is an embedded component and `<main>` is the host page's responsibility. Firing CRITICAL here would be a false alarm on out-of-scope markup. Logged as the MINOR structural finding above.\n- Form inputs without any label \u2014 **not fired.** The search input is correctly labeled (`:59-60`); credited as PASS.\n- Custom widget with no ARIA role \u2014 **fired** (interactive markers) \u2192 CRITICAL above.\n- Missing `lang` on `<html>` \u2014 **not fired.** `<html>` is out of component scope (host responsibility); N/A, not a defect of this artifact.\n\nFindings are code-level. One content-level dependency (existence of a redundant location list on the host page) is flagged for human verification in the summary.\n\n---\n\n## Perspective Audit Summary\n\n**Component/artifact reviewed:** Interactive Map With Mouse-Only Navigation (`MapInterface`, `map-interface-zoom-user.md`)\n**Perspectives escalated for deep review:** Magnification & Reflow (HIGH), Keyboard & Motor Access (HIGH), Screen Reader & Semantic Structure (MEDIUM)\n**Perspectives at LOW / not escalated (not reviewed):** Environmental Contrast, Vestibular & Motion Sensitivity, Auditory Access, Cognitive & Neurodivergent\n\n### Findings by Severity\n\n| Severity | Count |\n|---|---|\n| CRITICAL | 3 |\n| MAJOR | 4 |\n| MINOR | 5 |\n| ENHANCEMENT | 0 |\n\n### Perspectives That Passed\n\nNone. All three escalated perspectives produced findings. (Clean sub-areas credited as PASS: focus-indicator visibility and focus order for the focusable controls (2.4.7/2.4.13/2.4.3), search input labeling (3.3.2), heading structure (2.4.6), and no keyboard trap (2.1.2).)\n\n### Perspectives With Findings \u2014 Grouped by ARRM Role\n\n**Front-End Dev**\n- Pan + marker info keyboard-inoperable \u2014 Keyboard & Motor \u2014 CRITICAL \u2014 2.1.1 Keyboard\n- Drag-only pan, no click/tap alternative \u2014 Keyboard & Motor \u2014 CRITICAL \u2014 2.5.7 Dragging Movements (also 2.5.1)\n- Markers unexposed / info not in a11y tree \u2014 Screen Reader & Semantic \u2014 CRITICAL \u2014 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value (1.1.1)\n- `role=\"application\"` misused on a non-operable widget \u2014 Screen Reader & Semantic \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value\n- No status announcement on zoom change \u2014 Screen Reader & Semantic \u2014 MINOR \u2014 4.1.3 Status Messages\n- Section lacks accessible name / region \u2014 Screen Reader & Semantic \u2014 MINOR \u2014 1.3.1 Info and Relationships\n- Glyph vs accessible-name mismatch on zoom buttons \u2014 Keyboard & Motor \u2014 MINOR \u2014 2.5.3 Label in Name\n\n**Visual Design**\n- No reflow at 320px (fixed input width + absolutely-offset controls) \u2014 Magnification & Reflow \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 1.4.10 Reflow\n- Zoom targets 18\u00d718 below 24\u00d724 with 2px spacing \u2014 Keyboard & Motor \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 2.5.8 Target Size (Minimum)\n- Fixed control/popup sizes clip at 200% text zoom \u2014 Magnification & Reflow \u2014 MINOR \u2014 1.4.4 Resize Text\n- Fixed-width popup clips under text-spacing overrides \u2014 Magnification & Reflow \u2014 MINOR \u2014 1.4.12 Text Spacing\n\n**UX Design**\n- Hover-only popup: no Escape, no focus trigger \u2014 Magnification & Reflow \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 1.4.13 Content on Hover or Focus\n\n**Content Author**\n- (No content-authoring\u2013owned defects; caption/transcript/alt-editorial items out of scope. One human-verification dependency below.)\n\n### Open Questions Requiring Human Verification\n\n- **Is there a redundant text list of the same locations and details elsewhere on the host page?** This is the pivot for the Screen Reader 4.1.2 severity: with no text equivalent, the markers finding is CRITICAL (map is the sole carrier of location data); with a redundant accessible list present, it is MAJOR. Cannot be confirmed from this component's source. `[Human verification required \u2014 cannot be confirmed from source]`\n- **Does the host page provide a `<main>` landmark and a page `<title>`?** Assumed yes at component scope; confirm on the integrated page. `[Human verification required \u2014 cannot be confirmed from source]`\n\n### Recommended Next Step\n\n**BLOCK** \u2014 3 CRITICAL findings (2.1.1 keyboard inoperability of pan + markers, 2.5.7 drag-only pan with no alternative, 4.1.2 screen-reader-inaccessible location data). Do not ship until the map exposes a keyboard/single-pointer interaction model and a screen-reader-accessible representation of the location markers and their details. The 4 MAJOR findings should be resolved in the same pass; the 5 MINOR findings can follow.\n\n---\n\n## Contract-Compatible Evidence Findings (new CRITICAL/MAJOR)\n\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: map-pan-markers-keyboard-inoperable\nfingerprint: 7f3a9c21e0d4b8a2\nsource: perspective-audit Keyboard & Motor Access checklist\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 2.1.1 Keyboard\nsection_508_fpc_context: Revised Section 508 incorporates WCAG 2.0 2.1.1 (A) \u2014 applicable\nseverity: CRITICAL\nperspective_alarms: keyboard_motor=HIGH, screen_reader_semantic=MEDIUM\nevidence: map-interface-zoom-user.md:33-46 (mouse-only pan), :88-89 (marker hover handlers), :82-91 (marker `<div>` with no tabIndex/role/keydown)\nreproduction_steps: source review only \u2014 Tab through the component: focus reaches search and the two zoom buttons; no path focuses the map for panning or any marker to reveal info\nexpected_behavior: keyboard users can pan the map and open each marker's details via focus + Enter/Space/Arrow keys\nactual_behavior: panning and marker info are pointer-only; markers are not focusable\ntrend: new\n\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: map-pan-drag-only-no-alternative\nfingerprint: b4e8d0a61c93f752\nsource: perspective-audit Keyboard & Motor Access checklist\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 2.5.7 Dragging Movements (and 2.5.1 Pointer Gestures)\nsection_508_fpc_context: 2.5.7/2.5.1 are WCAG 2.1/2.2 criteria \u2014 beyond the Section 508 WCAG 2.0 baseline; treat as WCAG 2.2 AA in scope\nseverity: CRITICAL\nperspective_alarms: keyboard_motor=HIGH\nevidence: map-interface-zoom-user.md:33-46 \u2014 pan computed from mousedown\u2192mousemove\u2192mouseup client-coordinate deltas; no click/tap equivalent\nreproduction_steps: source review only \u2014 attempt to pan without a sustained drag path; no button, tap, or click-to-recenter alternative exists\nexpected_behavior: a single-pointer, non-drag/non-path action can pan or recenter the map\nactual_behavior: panning requires a click-and-drag path gesture with no alternative\ntrend: new\n\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: map-markers-screenreader-inaccessible\nfingerprint: c9f21d7e5a6b3048\nsource: perspective-audit Screen Reader & Semantic Structure checklist\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value (with 1.1.1 Non-text Content)\nsection_508_fpc_context: Revised Section 508 incorporates WCAG 2.0 4.1.2 and 1.1.1 (A) \u2014 applicable\nseverity: CRITICAL\nperspective_alarms: screen_reader_semantic=MEDIUM (audit finds under-weighted; proposes HIGH)\nevidence: map-interface-zoom-user.md:82-98 (non-semantic markers, hover-gated detail render), :91 (aria-label on generic div), :66 (role=\"application\" suppresses reading cursor)\nreproduction_steps: source review only \u2014 marker detail text (m.info) is rendered only while activePopup === m.id, so it never enters the accessibility tree for AT\nexpected_behavior: each location and its details are present in the accessibility tree with correct name/role, independent of pointer hover\nactual_behavior: markers expose no reliable name/role and details are absent from the a11y tree; the map's data is unreadable by AT\ntrend: new\n\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: map-role-application-misuse\nfingerprint: 2d6ac41f9be70513\nsource: perspective-audit Screen Reader & Semantic Structure checklist\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value; WAI-ARIA APG application-role guidance\nsection_508_fpc_context: Revised Section 508 incorporates WCAG 2.0 4.1.2 (A) \u2014 applicable\nseverity: MAJOR\nperspective_alarms: screen_reader_semantic=MEDIUM\nevidence: map-interface-zoom-user.md:63-73 \u2014 role=\"application\" with only mouse/wheel handlers, no focusable descendants or key handlers\nreproduction_steps: source review only \u2014 role=\"application\" instructs AT to pass keystrokes to a widget that implements no keyboard model\nexpected_behavior: application role used only with a complete keyboard interaction model; otherwise a region/group role\nactual_behavior: reading commands are suppressed while nothing inside is operable\ntrend: new\n\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: map-reflow-320-fixed-widths\nfingerprint: e15b7c8340a2d9f6\nsource: perspective-audit Magnification & Reflow checklist\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 1.4.10 Reflow\nsection_508_fpc_context: 1.4.10 is a WCAG 2.1/2.2 criterion \u2014 beyond the Section 508 WCAG 2.0 baseline; treat as WCAG 2.2 AA in scope\nseverity: MAJOR\nperspective_alarms: magnification_reflow=HIGH\nevidence: map-interface-zoom-user.md:123-125 (search-input width 280px + padding), :118 (page padding 24px), :161-164 (map-controls absolute top/right offsets)\nreproduction_steps: source review only \u2014 at 320px CSS width the labeled input (~304px border-box) plus 48px page padding exceeds the viewport, forcing horizontal scroll; controls do not reflow\nexpected_behavior: content reflows to a single column at 320px with no two-axis scrolling\nactual_behavior: fixed input width and absolutely-offset controls break reflow at 320px\ntrend: new\n\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: map-hover-popup-no-dismiss-no-focus\nfingerprint: 9a0f5e2b7d1c46e8\nsource: perspective-audit Magnification & Reflow checklist\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 1.4.13 Content on Hover or Focus\nsection_508_fpc_context: 1.4.13 is a WCAG 2.1/2.2 criterion \u2014 beyond the Section 508 WCAG 2.0 baseline; treat as WCAG 2.2 AA in scope\nseverity: MAJOR\nperspective_alarms: magnification_reflow=HIGH, keyboard_motor=HIGH\nevidence: map-interface-zoom-user.md:88-98 \u2014 popup shown on mouseenter, removed on mouseleave; no Escape handler; no focus trigger\nreproduction_steps: source review only \u2014 popup cannot be dismissed via Escape and cannot be triggered without a pointer hover\nexpected_behavior: hover/focus content is dismissible (Escape), hoverable, persistent, and also focus-triggerable\nactual_behavior: popup is hover-only and not dismissible without moving the pointer\ntrend: new\n\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: map-zoom-target-size-18px\nfingerprint: 4c7e1a09f6b2538d\nsource: perspective-audit Keyboard & Motor Access checklist\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 2.5.8 Target Size (Minimum)\nsection_508_fpc_context: 2.5.8 is a WCAG 2.2 criterion \u2014 beyond the Section 508 WCAG 2.0 baseline; treat as WCAG 2.2 AA in scope\nseverity: MAJOR\nperspective_alarms: keyboard_motor=HIGH, magnification_reflow=HIGH\nevidence: map-interface-zoom-user.md:166-168 (.zoom-control 18px \u00d7 18px), :161-164 (.map-controls gap 2px)\nreproduction_steps: source review only \u2014 measure control box: 18\u00d718 CSS px, below the 24\u00d724 minimum, with 2px spacing that fails the undersized-target spacing exception\nexpected_behavior: interactive targets \u226524\u00d724 CSS px (or 24px spacing offset)\nactual_behavior: 18\u00d718 tar